# Baseline – Do Not Break

This project has a **baseline** checkpoint. The following must continue to work; do not remove or break them when making other changes.

## Reading theater & flip cards

- **Route:** `/reading/theater` shows passage (left) + coach flip cards (right).
- **Flip card behaviour:** Front shows one text → user clicks → card flips (3D rotateY) → back shows different text. Click again (or OK on back) flips to front. **No mirroring** of text on either side.
- **Implementation:** CSS `.flip-card`, `.flip-card-inner`, `.flip-card-face`, `.flip-card-back` and `backface-visibility` in `app/globals.css`; `FlipCoachCard` in `modules/reading/PassageOnlyView.tsx`. See the "REQUIRED FLIP CARD BEHAVIOUR" comment in that file.
- **Cards:** 3 cards; theme-aware (use `bg-surface`, `border-border`) so they adapt to dark mode and stay clearly identifiable as cards.

## Dark mode

- **Toggle:** Sun/moon in header (and on reading theater when header is hidden). Preference stored in `localStorage` key `mcq-theme`; respects `prefers-color-scheme` when unset.
- **Implementation:** `.dark` on `<html>`, CSS variables in `app/globals.css`, `ThemeProvider` + inline script in `app/layout.tsx`, `@custom-variant dark` for Tailwind. UI using theme tokens (e.g. `bg-bg`, `text-text`, `bg-surface`, `border-border`) must keep adapting to light/dark.

## When changing code

- Preserve: front text → click → flip → back text; no mirrored content; dark mode toggle and theme-aware surfaces/borders.
- Test: flip cards on `/reading/theater` and light/dark toggle after your changes.
